The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, which are both covered by the Computer Science sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks and the focus on learning also suggest the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the mention of visual QA domains and the use of text as input suggest the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
